parts.markscheme:
An input transducer/sensor converts a physical property (e.g., light level, temperature, soil moisture) into an electrical signal <marks>1</marks>;
This signal represents the physical data in a form that the computer system can receive and process <marks>1</marks>;

[2 marks]

Computers operate using discrete binary/digital data (0s and 1s) and cannot process continuous analog voltages directly <marks>1</marks>;
The ADC samples the continuous analog signal at intervals and converts it into a digital representation/numeric value that the microprocessor can manipulate <marks>1</marks>;

